Now is indescribably horrifying and terrifying.

My hope, though, is that young people of the world see this as opportunity. 

That now is their time, their chance to live the 60's. Be cooler than their parents. Fulfill the hippie dream, save the world.

"And know they love you" https://t.co/YXe1G0C8su

I attract young people. They tell me how cool our HIPEVAN is. They love my ski helmets. They love what we eat. They tell me how much they love our music from back then. 

I'm humbled by their comments. But my life isn't by design. I do what turns me on. https://t.co/Uy3d4NlblY

The hippie dream is still alive, just not fulfilled. 

NFT projects have hippie references in their names - "hallucinations", "synthetic", "peaceful", etc. They have "trippy" traits. Most NFTs are colorful, just like the hippies were. Tie dye was the OG of street wear.

The hippie dream of the 60's fell way short. 

They left Woodstock, got caught up in consumption - career, vacations, paying for kids college, stuff.

Now wen we look back we see our mistakes. We see the pursuit of everything was mainly the pursuit of nothing.

Maybe share with others, so they can get to know people they'll never meet.

Then have a listen to Teach Your Children. Watch the video, get how then is so today. BTW that's Jerry Garcia on pedal steel guitar.

https://t.co/cGdF4L7myI

bc I'm so over wondering if my wallet has anything left. I'm sick of the scams, the shitheads, charlatans, tomfoolery, and all the bs that's everywhere in this circus called better. It's all a fucking downer.

Then came the Internet.

The same could be happening here. 

I used to do a lot of LSD. I bought fucking art magnets (WTF was I thinking!). I get it, I'm out there.

But it's not an hallucination to think all this is just a beta. One big test case for the real thing.

And if they did, I'd be all over it and I bet so would you. Because it'd be fast, trustworthy, low cost, someone to help wen something goes wrong.

In the late 80's The Baby Bells used pay-per call as a proving ground to see what consumers appetite was for information.

If I'm Microsoft, Google, or Apple I'm watching this circus called the future, saying to myself, "You know. We could make our own chain. It'd be secure, it'd solve all the problems that exist. We'd run these yahoos out of town".
